# Accessibility Rules (WCAG AA+)

Never sacrifice accessibility for aesthetics. Target: Lighthouse Accessibility 100, WCAG 2.2 AA minimum.

## Structure and semantics

- One `<h1>` per page; heading levels never skip (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Landmarks: `<header>`, `<nav aria-label="Main">`, `<main id="main">`, `<footer>`; multiple navs get distinct `aria-label`s
- Skip link (`.skip-link`) as the first focusable element, visually hidden until focused
- Use native elements before ARIA: `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation, `<details>` for simple disclosure
- Lists are real `<ul>/<ol>`; tables have `<th scope>`; images have meaningful `alt` (or `alt=""` if decorative)

## Keyboard

- Every interactive element reachable and operable by keyboard alone (Tab/Shift+Tab, Enter/Space, Escape, arrows where idiomatic)
- Visible focus: style `:focus-visible` with a 2px+ outline token (`--color-primary` based), offset 2px; never `outline: none` without replacement
- Mobile nav drawer: trap focus while open, close on Escape, return focus to the toggle button
- Custom widgets (tabs, accordion, carousel) follow WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices keyboard patterns

## ARIA

- Toggle buttons: `aria-expanded` + `aria-controls`
- Accordions: button in heading, `aria-expanded`, region with `aria-labelledby` (or use `<details>/<summary>`)
- Tabs: `role="tablist"/"tab"/"tabpanel"`, `aria-selected`, roving tabindex, arrow-key navigation
- Live feedback (form success/error, async states): `role="status"` or `aria-live="polite"`
- Icon-only buttons: `aria-label`; decorative SVGs: `aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"`

## Forms

- Every input has a programmatically associated `<label>` (`for`/`id`)
- Required fields: `required` + visible indicator explained in text, not color alone
- Errors: inline message linked via `aria-describedby`, `aria-invalid="true"` on the field, focus moved to first invalid field on submit
- Autocomplete attributes on identity fields (`autocomplete="email"`, `name`, etc.)

## Visual

- Contrast: 4.5:1 normal text, 3:1 large text (≥24px or ≥18.7px bold), 3:1 UI components and focus indicators — in BOTH themes
- Never convey meaning by color alone (pair with icon/text)
- Touch targets ≥ 44×44px (or 24px with sufficient spacing)
- Text resizable to 200% without loss of content; layout survives 320px width
- `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` disables/reduces all non-essential animation
